<sect1 id="index_1intro_sec">
<title>Introduction</title><para><ref refid="class_qt_pass" kindref="compound">QtPass</ref> is a multi-platform GUI for pass, the standard unix password manager.</para>
<para><ulink url="https://qtpass.org/">https://qtpass.org/</ulink></para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="index_1install_sec">
<title>Installation</title><sect2 id="index_1dependencies">
<title>Dependencies</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ref refid="class_qt_pass" kindref="compound">QtPass</ref> requires Qt 5.15 or later.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The Linguist package is required to compile the translations.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>For use of the fallback icons the SVG library is required.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>At runtime the only real dependency is gpg2 but to make the most of it, you&apos;ll need git and pass too.</para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="index_1source">
<title>From source</title><para>On most *nix systems all you need is:</para>
<para><computeroutput>qmake &amp;&amp; make &amp;&amp; make install</computeroutput> </para>
</sect2>
</sect1>
